commit.message:
Merge branch 'hotfix-3.2.1' into 'master'

Bumblebee 3.2.1

Closes GH-394, GH-400

Supplemental note for packagers

busid.conf needs to be removed in order for optirun to work.
Bumblebee 3.2.1

Unsplit "Device" section across xorg.conf files

This fixes the widely faced issue in Bumblebee 3.2
Correct index of -modulepath argument

Merge branch 'release-3.2' into 'master'

Release 3.2 of Bumblebee

This closes GH-381.
Install xorg.conf.d files, use path from Makefile

Yet another fail...

xorg.conf.d wasn't 'made'.
Merge branch 'develop' into release-3.2
Stick for VirtualGL

Merge branch 'release-3.2' into develop

Backport release-3.2 in develop.
Forgot to update name of udev rule here...

Updated release notes for 3.2

Reworked text about primus. We need people to try it, so that everyone
usecases are covered.
Updated and unified copyright

Fixed release notes

Two lines were mixed.
Add 3.2 release notes
Changed version number to 3.2

Renamed 99-remove-nvidia-dev.rules to 99-bumblebee-nvidia-dev.rules

This name was consufing and not reflecting the new purpose of this file.
The fact we changed the file name will also force packagers to take care
of the underlying changes.

xorg.conf: New scheme

Unified Device[01] to DiscreteNvidia.

Moved BusID to a separate file in xorg.conf.d.

Added AutoAddGPUs false to xorg.conf.nvidia.

Removed screen section from xorg.conf.nouveau (this is useless if you don't set anything special).

Merge pull request #382 from ralfjung-e/develop

Print more options when dumping configuration
Print more options when dumping configuration
Implement --no-xorg (GH-89)
Add udev rules to create device files

Add "none" accel/display bridge

The proper way to run nvidia settings is

    optirun -b none nvidia-settings -c :8
start_secondary: bool arg: need_secondary, return: success
Remove unused status_secondary
Factor out PM and module (un)loading in bbsecondary.c
Add support for passing -configdir to secondary X (GH-222)
